```suggestion
      rw [reassoc_of% e.functor_unit_comp]
```
There are a lot of reassoc attributes missing in `Equivalence.lean`, so if you like you can go ahead and add them, otherwise I will get around to it eventually.
I can add the them. Should every lemma which is an equality of two morphisms have the `reassoc` attribute, and `reassoc (attr := simp)` if it's a simp lemma?
I just added them, but I guess it makes sense to do that change as a separate PR?
Thanks! I think it's fine to do it as part of this PR.

Since the LHS isn't a composition, the reassoc version is only useful for rewriting the other direction, so this should just be
```suggestion
@[reassoc, simp]
```
This one and the three lemmas below don't have compositions in their statement, so they don't need the `reassoc` attribute.
The docstring should talk about effective epimorphisms.
